    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "This is understandably difficult to do for async methods: the user usually has work to do after sending the response (cleanup, calling `RequestMyMethod` again, etc), and there's more state to keep track of (has the response already been sent?), so I'm only suggesting doing this for sync methods.\r\n\r\nAsync programming and exceptions really don't play well with each other, anyway."
